Intake-2021: Picture It

  • Summary
  • Screenshot
  • Interesting Files
  • 7z2John
  • Getting the flag

Summary

“Picture It” is a challenge I made for the beginner ctf “IntakeCTF”.

From a memory dump, you can use the screenshot volatility command to get a clipping of the screen when the memory was dumped. Using this, you can see a pastebin link in one of the window titles. This contains passwords for different services. One of the passwords is for word documents and it just so happens that an encrypted word document can be found. After decrypting the word document more passwords are inside. Looking at more files on the system, secrets.7z is somewhat suspicious, using 7z2john, the dump can be cracked and the flag found inside.

Screenshot

Viewing the image with volatility:

The profile name is given which should speed things up a little. However other than being XP, there is not much help from this.

Looking at running processes:

There’s not much of interest. DumpIt.exe appears to just be a program used to dump memory of an operating system so probably won’t be too much use.

Notepad.exe is running so perhaps a file is being edited. Looking at a a screenshot of the screen at the time of the dump:

python2 vol.py -f /tmp/memdump screenshot --dump-dir /tmp/memdump/dumpdir

There’s quite a few windows open but the most interesting one is indeed the notepad:

Going to that pastebin link gives:

Interesting Files

So there could be encrypted files we’re able to decrypt:

python2 vol.py -f /tmp/memdump --profile WinXPSP3x86 filescan

Shows some interesting files
